reviews_data.review_text: Great sandwich and lemonade flight! Was not busy during my visit which was nice. Will come back to try their coffee selection! They have a lot of flavor options and fun combinations. And also, they have ice cream. Win-win for everyone. Also the employees were great!
Great coffee and good chicken salad!!
Atmosphere is safe for the whole family. Great food, good prices,  friendly staff. Enjoyed.
We stopped in for lunch. Never been here. But it was so good. The sandwiches were perfect tasting and size for the price. Thank you for being here. Hope to be back soon!!
This place is the cutest! Everyone is so friendly and welcoming! My husband and I got the caramel macchiato and frozen caramel frappe. Delicious! 10/10 recommend!

The barista was excellent! She had a really nice, welcoming, and warm personality. She assumed that she wasn't going to be able to make me a vegan mocha latte. But she took the time to assess the chocolate they use and we found that they do in fact have a vegan friendly option there. She made me a really delicious latte! The place appeared to not have any other vegan options though so that's why I rated it so low. But definitely a five star for service! And a pretty decent atmosphere as well.
I have very specific dietary needs and they were very helpful and accommodating. I will definitely be back and next time with my family! Thank you.

The turkey bacon panini is delicious!
Great food and coffee. Staff is great. You gotta get the quiche

reviews_data.review_text: I’m the most offended by the fact that their homemade ranch tastes like Italian dressing. They have a house blend that they put on things that’s basically Italian dressing (olive oil, Italian seasonings, garlic, and vinegar)…I’m pretty sure they add it to the ranch. If I wanted Italian, I wouldn’t have ordered ranch. I didn’t order the panini because it also comes on the panini. I’m not sure why they are adding it to foods that don’t need it, I expected clean and simple sandwiches and melts from a small cafe. Good creamy buttermilk ranch. The salad was very fresh with crunchy cucumbers and freshly cut tomatoes. Cute little crunchy croutons. Coffee is pretty good but they are trying to do so much with all of the different drink flights and types of coffee, makes it hard to do things well. Soup was microwaved very obviously, which I’m not sure makes sense with it being a soup of the day? The “chicken and dumpling” soup was very gummy. It had carrots and potatoes but no visible chicken. Just thought that was strange. Soft potatoes on top of soft dumplings. Microwaved so hot and it was so thick it was hard to eat. I did like that the servers wore gloves when they carrying food. Service was alright, it’s definitely a relaxed bunch who likes to chat and the food takes a while. It’s not busy at all but they don’t deliver food or come to bus your tables, I think that would be a nice touch for a small business. I just think overall things could be improved with simple crowd pleasing improvements.

The staff was very friendly and kind. However, they need more training and practice when making hot lattes. The foam was not steamed properly, and the flavor was not mixed into the espresso…leaving the first sips unsweetened, and the last sips sickeningly sweet. Please make sure your employees get proper training for future customers.
Best service ever, always know our orders and always happy to see everyone when you walk in the door

What a great spot! I love places with this that mix a great space with a variety of drinks and food. I had an iced London Fog latte which was pretty good (a little artificial vanilla flavor I think) and an AMAZING egg and cheese bagel sandwich. I'm still dreaming about the sandwich 🤣
The chicken salad sandwich was delicious. My best friend raves about the waffles, bagel sandwiches and the turkey panini. Definitely a cute little local cafe to go to!

The coffee was sickeningly sweet and disgusting, the place smelled very strange, and while the baristas seemed nice they also seemed lost. Too bad there aren't enough good coffee shops in this town to compete with this place.
Great place to eat, food was delicious and service was great.

Incredibly cute cafe with coffee, tea, sandwiches, and ice cream. My husband had a Big Red sandwich, and I had the chicken salad croissant. Fresh and delicious! One of the employees let us try a cinnamon toast frappe, which was the icing on the cake.

Order at the counter and have a seat! The ladies working behind the counter were very sweet and did a great job making everything.
My favorite coffee shop. The staff are always friendly and make delicious coffee.
Love the place,great service, and very friendly staff, unfortunately awful coffee.

Love the environment and food HOWEVER, I come in quite often and I noticed that there is usually one young lady with bangs doing a lot of the work. Today I came in to this employee taking orders and making the drinks and food. I was waiting on my food and she was busy making some other people’s drinks. The other employee with brown hair went to the back and sat on her phone instead of making my food. The employee with the bangs made my food after she got done and apologized for the wait. The employee with the bangs always provides good and fast service but you people have her working too hard. From the experiences I have had, she does the work of two people while the other goes on their phone. The lady with the brown hair and freckles I have not had a good experience with ever. She should get fired if this is a reoccurring thing and the other sweet girl with black hair should get a raise. Do better big red’s cafe.
Good food all around, friendly and helpful staff also.  Belgian waffles have a nice, sweet crunch as a surprise.  Spinach wrap was very good.
Everything was immaculate, from the service to the food to the coffee.
Seasonal favorites: iced blueberry macchiato and mixed-berry danish. Very helpful staff. Still want to try their waffles.
We had coffee. It was truly delicious 😋
Good coffee, boba, and food.

I arrived 20 minutes before closing. I ordered two lattes, one hot and one iced. As I'm watching them make my drinks I realized that they were not using the espresso machine, but instead pouring regular coffee in the cups. I asked them about it and they said that they had already cleaned the espresso machine. They knew this when I ordered and did not tell me. Essentially, they charged me for two lattes and gave me two coffees. They weren't even good.
Great food and excellent customer service
The Ham Melt sandwich is very good and tasty.  The pickels are small and dried out.
What a great place!

I personally love going to big reds on a nice day, buying myself a turkey bacon panini and sometimes I treat myself to a coffee. The service is always fantastic, the food is unbelievably amazing. I love what they did with the place.

I would highly recommend to anyone who is looking for that iconic Cafe experience.

My wife and were traveling through Kings Mountain and wanted to grab some lunch. Very warm welcoming. Food was delicious! Service was excellent! I had the BLT and a side of potato salad. My wife had a Summer Berry Spinach Salad and a side of chicken salad. All fresh and very tasty!! Would recommend!
Refreshing atmosphere at the edge of Kings Mountain. I'll be back on my next date with my wife.

I had never been before and wasn't sure what to expect.
The lemonade flight was fun.

The waffles are the store bought kind with the sugar in them so I wouldn't have needed that syrup I poured in the but otherwise good.
Love this place! Best coffee in town, can't go wrong with any food here either!

My family and I LOVED this place! My caramel latté and my father’s americano were just what we needed on a rainy day after visiting a local festival. I wish we had more time to stay and enjoy the atmosphere and we can’t wait to go back. It’s unexpected to find somewhere that reminds you of Lake Tahoe or Colorado in the Carolinas, so as native Californians, this was an extra special treat. Their pastries were very much enjoyed as well - I may or may not have stolen half of my mom’s! Next time I will check out their lunch menu because everything looked delicious with nothing but happy customers all around.
Best place to grab a great chocolate frappe!!!🤤🤤🤤😋… better not leave without breakfast , brunch, or lunch… save room for dessert or save it for latter🤤🤤🤤🤤🤤😋😋😋😋…WELL WORTH IT!!!

reviews_data.review_text: Great food, drinks, and service. The prices are awesome too.
The iced coffee is wonderful!

Absolutely love their coffee.
But what I love more is their courage of standing on faith. Not many people are willing to share their love of God. Especially businesses, because of fear of losing customers.
But Big Red’s, gladly plays worship music.

The sandwich was piled with rubbery bacon, and I can only assume it was to make up for the lack of egg. It was as thin as a drink coaster, and barely noticeable with any bite. The bread was wonderful however.  Soft and buttery.

Quaint place.
Staff was pleasant and coffee was good.

Stopped in for a quick lunch before a hike. Grabbed a couple of sandwiches, which were good. Chicken salad can get messy. I usually get quiche, but they had already sold out. Very friendly service and cute place next to Patriot Jack's.  Only place I've seen a coffee flight.
Ice cream selection was small, but our friend found a flavor she liked.
Popped in for lunch after hiking Crowder’s Mtn. Great food, cool atmosphere, and super friendly staff. Gonna be my go to after a hike.
Love this place

I have been wanting to try their coffee flights and after seeing a post on their social media I decided get me one.
As I ordered the flight I asked the lady if I could change one of the drinks because I didn’t like the flavor, she rudely told me “no, because if I do it for you I have to do it for everyone else” , I was the only ordering at the time . When she started making the flight I noticed that she was  using on plastics cups, I quickly asked her if they were not using glass cup anymore because I just seem a post on their media earlier that day and she reply with “no because then we have to wash them” . After she gave us the drinks they were a mess and  we could barely grab the cups without getting our hands dirty. Two of the drinks were really good. The other two tasted like water with a little bit of flavor.
Great coffee and great atmosphere!!! I'm glad I was lead to this place!!!
This is a very charming lovely cafe! If you're in the KM area, pay this place a visit. Great service and food. Coffee is excellent here as well!
All prepackaged food, both my son and I felt awful after eating there. Club chair arms are tore up. The servers were friendly. I will not return

Amazing and cute breakfast spot (they also do lunch but I was here for breakfast) with fresh food and service that makes you feel right at home. The coffee is incredible and the location is very convenient!

Adorable spot to grab breakfast or lunch. Refreshing to enjoy food without music blaring in my ear. Pretty awesome they offer breakfast all day, have a wide coffee variety plus ice cream and danishes. The food is as pictured and tasted great!

Honestly if I was the boss there everyone would be wearing a hair net this is not the first time I have found hair in my food

I do appreciate the refund though but this could all be avoided by HAIR NETS
Good service. Very nice place. Priced reasonable. Nice atmosphere.
First time there. But it was a good choice for breakfast!! Will definitely be back!
Delicious drink options and a really fun atmosphere!
Best coffee/cafe place in the area
Alright for passing by and grabbing a sandwich and coffee.
Great little place to get a delicious coffee and something fun to snack on. The buffalo chicken salad sandwich was great!!

Went in for a sandwich at 3:15 and was told they were closing soon and were only making coffee. Their sign says open till 4 pm.

Will not be back.

Urge everyone to not come here for food!!
Lots of fun options for food and drinks. Sandwiches, Belgian waffles, mini doughnuts, ice cream, and all the coffee shop options.

Big Red's Cafe excels not only in savory delights but also in crafting a delightful coffee and ice cream experience. The menu features rich and aromatic coffee blends, catering to both connoisseurs and casual drinkers. The ice cream selection is a sweet revelation, offering indulgent flavors that satisfy every craving. From classic vanilla to innovative creations, each scoop is a treat. The cafe's warm and inviting atmosphere provides an ideal setting to enjoy a cup of freshly brewed coffee or savor a decadent ice cream sundae. Big Red's Cafe seamlessly combines savory and sweet for a well-rounded and enjoyable culinary journey.

Loved this cozy county log cabin like brunch Cafe! It serves great Panini style sandwiches with different styles and flavors of coffee but the best part is that it's located 5 minutes away from Crowders Mountain State Park and is a perfect spot after a strenuous hike! More detailed video with full description is on my social media accounts called @travelguidenc on Instagram,  tiktok and YouTube! Website coming soon!

Stood there about nine minutes as person behind counter had a conversation with other customers.  Then totally ignored us and went into back.  Other lady behind counter was very busy making orders, but did finally ask if we were ready.  By now we were perturbed and left.   As we drove about twenty minutes to get here, and was our first visit, I sincerely doubt we will return.  Also will not recommend to anyone.

I 100% recommend Big Red's Cafe! Friendly people,  with great food including breakfast and lunch options.  They can make a lot of different drinks including shakes.  They have ice cream, muffins,  cake pops, and other little treats.  There are a few things for the littles as well.  There are good options for seating inside and outside with a nice view of Crowders Mountain.
It had a nice ambiance and was relaxing. Nice place to sit for a while or just to run in real quick. I had a chicken Caesar salad and mocha frappe. I would definitely go back. 👍

Big Red's Cafe is a great place to meet for coffee or get some work done. They do a great job with the drinks, and it is hard to resist those little doughnuts made right in front of you! I would love for them to invest in a more improved venting system as you do leave the place smelling like the doughnut machine, but overall, I love coming to Big Red's, and I love the fact that it seems to be really growing in business! I also love the local products they feature on their shelves for sale- it is such a relaxed atmosphere; it is fun to do a little shopping while hanging out.

reviews_data.review_text: I’m the most offended by the fact that their homemade ranch tastes like Italian dressing. They have a house blend that they put on things that’s basically Italian dressing (olive oil, Italian seasonings, garlic, and vinegar)…I’m pretty sure they add it to the ranch. If I wanted Italian, I wouldn’t have ordered ranch. I didn’t order the panini because it also comes on the panini. I’m not sure why they are adding it to foods that don’t need it, I expected clean and simple sandwiches and melts from a small cafe. Good creamy buttermilk ranch. The salad was very fresh with crunchy cucumbers and freshly cut tomatoes. Cute little crunchy croutons. Coffee is pretty good but they are trying to do so much with all of the different drink flights and types of coffee, makes it hard to do things well. Soup was microwaved very obviously, which I’m not sure makes sense with it being a soup of the day? The “chicken and dumpling” soup was very gummy. It had carrots and potatoes but no visible chicken. Just thought that was strange. Soft potatoes on top of soft dumplings. Microwaved so hot and it was so thick it was hard to eat. I did like that the servers wore gloves when they carrying food. Service was alright, it’s definitely a relaxed bunch who likes to chat and the food takes a while. It’s not busy at all but they don’t deliver food or come to bus your tables, I think that would be a nice touch for a small business. I just think overall things could be improved with simple crowd pleasing improvements.

The staff was very friendly and kind. However, they need more training and practice when making hot lattes. The foam was not steamed properly, and the flavor was not mixed into the espresso…leaving the first sips unsweetened, and the last sips sickeningly sweet. Please make sure your employees get proper training for future customers.

It had grapes, pineapple, cantaloupe, honeydew melon, mandarin oranges, and the owner offered to add strawberries and blueberries.
